I would like to give a neutral review. I really enjoyed the game but for its current state I cannot give it a positive review. It really needs A LOT of improvement and optimisation. I finished my first game on the highest difficult. The story was really fun although the ending is bit weird. You get asked for two options/missions and then the credits roll?

Because the discussion page is overloaded right now I’ll post my recommendations here and hope one of the devs will pick it up. I will keep this review updated for future patches. 

1.	More workers per hub + better worker optimization. In the end when I had 300 workers it still did not solve the supply and demand. I had to reset a lot of buildings to get resources delivered.  I think making multiple workers per hub possible will improve congestion. 
2.	Resources. For such a big planet some resource do get really scarce. And I’ve seen multiple reports on the discussions by other people. Maybe adding like end game functions where you can have some sort infinite supply? Like water, what’s the point of creating oceans and lakes when u can’t use the water and keep relying on ice? Another possibility would be ocean mining and exploration. A lot gets lost in the process of terraforming. 
3.	Storage and logistics. The storage centres as is don’t work properly. Drones deliver resources but when demand is getting high the will not haul it from the same centres. The same can be applied to the overall logistics. A lot of resources get stuck in one place. Even when I had a worldwide hyperloop network, workers sometimes still travelled basic routes to deliver goods.

Some quality of life improvements would be:
4.	More personal key bindings + options;
5.	In late game adding notifications when a project is finished in orbit would really help;
6.	Ways of halving your combat drones swarm (if there is one let me know please);
7.	In the structure tab options to select and deselect all or specific groups;
8.	Maybe automatic road upgrades. It gets really micro and tedious if you have a big base.
